National President of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Rev Olasupo Ayokunle, Wednesday decried the precarious situation Nigeria has found itself, assertng that the nation was passing through a difficult phase.Ayokunle made this assertion in Ibadan, Oyo State capital at the ongoing weeklong 37th Holy Ghost Convention of the Sword of the Spirit Ministries a.k.a Christ Life Church, Ibadan, headed by Bishop Francis Wale Oke.According to him: “Things are not going on right in Nigeria. Our nation is passing through a difficult phase.”The CAN President, who is also the National President, Baptist Convention, however, expressed the optimism that God would intervene to salvage the situation.Confessing that steering affairs of the association had not been easy, Ayokunle pointed out that the body was not a political party but rather an organisation out to defend the interest of Christians in the country.